      <div class="msgContentFrame">Hittign the report button basically puts up a notification box for all the admins similar to what you see when you get a new PM or when a thread you are following gets a reply. We click that, it takes us to a page with the report and a link to the reported post. We then either clear the report or take action on it. As long as you don't spam the report system or somethign like that, they usually take seconds to deal with and we don't mind. <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Arch Duke Kaolian Drachensborn, lvl 90 Ranger, Unrest Server <br /><a href="/forum.html?forum=25" rel="external nofollow" title="www.zam.com/forum.html?forum=25">Tech support forum</a> | <a href="HTTP://www.zam.com/wiki/irc" rel="external nofollow" title="www.zam.com/wiki/irc">How to set Up zam IRC</a> | <a href="HTTP://www.zam.com/wiki/Frequently_Asked_Questions_(Support)" rel="external nofollow" title="www.zam.com/wiki/Frequently_Asked_Questions_(Support)">FAQ (Support)</a> | Mobile Zam: <a href="http://m.zam.com" title="http://m.zam.com" rel="external nofollow">http://m.zam.com</a> (Premium only) <br /><a href="HTTP://www.zam.com/wiki/Forum_Rules" rel="external" title="www.zam.com/wiki/Forum_Rules">Forum Rules</a> </div></div>
